Nigeria midfielder, Ebenezer Akinsanmiro has linked up with Serie A giants, Inter Milan from Nigeria Premier Football League club, Remo Stars. The youngster penned a four-year contract with the Nerazzurri. Akinsanmiro has joined the list of Nigerian players, who featured for Inter Milan. The likes of Nwankwo Kanu, Taribo West, Obafemi Martins, Obinna Nsofor, Joel Obi and Obiora Nwankwo were once in the books of the Italian club. The talented midfielder was a product of Remo Starsâ€™ academy team, Beyond Limits. Akinsanmiro was part of the Sky Blue Stars side that gained promotion to the NPFL in the 2020/21 season. He also featured for the Ikenne club last season.